  "title": "Golang Engineer",
  "description": "<p><br /><strong>Our client is one of the leading regional bank and one of Asia’s most respected digital banking institutions</strong>, recognized for its strong technology-first strategy, innovation culture, and large-scale transformation initiatives.</p><p>This is an excellent opportunity to join a <strong>high-impact engineering team</strong> building secure, scalable, and mission-critical systems that power millions of daily financial transactions.</p><p>Although structured as a <strong>1-year contract</strong>, this role offers <strong>long-term project continuity, strong renewal potential, and a completion bonus</strong>, making it an ideal platform for engineers looking to establish a stable and meaningful career in the banking/fintech space.</p><p>If you’re passionate about Golang and want exposure to enterprise-grade systems, this is a rare opportunity to work at scale within a highly reputable environment.</p><p>Mutiple headcounts - Only singaporean</p><h2>✨ What You’ll Do</h2><ul><li><p>Design, develop, and maintain backend services using <strong>Golang</strong></p></li><li><p>Build scalable APIs and microservices supporting digital banking platforms</p></li><li><p>Enhance system performance, reliability, and security</p></li><li><p>Work closely with architects, product teams, and senior engineers</p></li><li><p>Participate in code reviews, testing, and production deployments</p></li><li><p>Contribute to high-availability, regulated financial systems</p></li></ul><h2>✅ What We’re Looking For</h2><ol><li><p>1–3 years of experience in <strong>Golang development</strong> (fresh grads with strong projects/internships are welcome)</p></li><li><p>Understanding of RESTful APIs, microservices, and backend fundamentals</p></li><li><p>Experience with SQL/NoSQL databases</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Git, CI/CD, or cloud environments is a plus</p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving mindset and eagerness to learn<br /></p><p><strong>Next Step</strong></p><ul><li>Simply click on 'Apply here' or email to tamanna.bilandi@adecco.com to drop your resume.</li><li>All shortlisted candidates will be contacted.<br /></li></ul><p>Tamanna Bilandi</p><p>EA Licence No. 91C2918</p><p>Personnel Registration No. R2096241<br /></p></li></ol>",
